2.10	Komazawa_University	Komazawa University	Komazawa University (駒澤大學, Komazawa Daigaku,abbreviated as 駒大 Komadai) is one of the oldest universities in Japan. Its history starts in 1592, when a seminary was established to be a center of learning for the young monks of the Sōtō sect, one of the two main Zen Buddhist traditions in Japan.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bc/Komazawa_main.JPG/250px-Komazawa_main.JPG
